tracks.title: Yotto - Memento
tracks.description:
Pre-order Anjunadeep 07: http://po.st/Anjunadeep07
Release Date: 25 May
Beatport: http://po.st/MementoAzzurro

Talented Helsinki producer Yotto aka Otto Yliperttula is the latest signing to the Anjunadeep roster, debuting with a heavy-hitting two tracker “Memento / Azzurro”.

First heard in James Grant’s Anjunadeep Edition 50 mix “Memento” is a huge dancefloor weapon, echoing the bass-driven sounds of Jonas Rathsman and Dusky. Rolling low-end stabs surge through murky, atmospheric melodies leading to an epic breakdown.

“Azzurro” is another bass heavy roller, built around a growling groove that gives way to a nostalgic piano line and soaring pads, rising to a dramatic crescendo before dropping back into darkness.

tracks.description:

London based duo Solomon Grey first appeared on Anjunadeep with their much loved collaboration with Lane 8, ‘Diamonds’. They return to the label with John Monkman’s sublime remix of ‘Twilight’.

The remix began life as a bootleg after John heard the original during an episode of The Casual Vacancy on BBC1, which was scored by Solomon Grey. Unaware of their link to Anjunadeep, John sent the remix over and the rest if history!

With early support from Jonas Rathsman, Skream and Lane 8 amongst others, John’s remix is a soaring dancefloor weapon, built around haunting female vocals, a driving groove and emotive atmospherics.

tracks.title: Eats Everything feat Tiga Vs Audion - Dancing (Again!)
tracks.description:
Out now!! 

Buy ‘Dancing (Again!)’

Beatport: http://btprt.dj/1MO9zd5
iTunes - http://hyperurl.co/y8qi1q

http://www.facebook.com/methodrecords
http://twitter.com/MethodRecords

http://www.facebook.com/MrEatsEverything
http://twitter.com/eats_everything
http://soundcloud.com/eatseverything
http://www.youtube.com/MrEatsEverything

Dancing blurb (by Eats)
Dancing was born from playing at Bugged Out Weekender a few year back. I was playing my version of Ron Costa - Gez Uri & Breach had given me a copy of his track, Jack. I think I was  one of the first to have it & I just stuck the Jack vocal over the Ron Costa thing on the fly & when it dropped the place went mental. From that shit loads of people kept sending me videos asking what this track was etc so I thought fuck it, went into the studio & fucked about more with the Ron Costa record & put the Jack vocal on top & made into an edit which became the highlight of mine & a lot of my DJ friends sets. Forward on a year & Tiga & Audion - Lets Go Dancing had just surfaced & it was massive. Jack was obviously a chart song by then so I had stopped playing it. I heard Lets Go Dancing & thought aha, this could replace the Jack vocal!! So I messaged the lovely Tiga, asked for the acapella & he obliged. I went back in the studio, edited the Jack track with the Tiga vocal & the behemoth was born. That was way over a year ago & it's been going mad in my sets & lots of other people's. So many people have been asking for this record so Disclosure & The Method boys came up with a plan to release it. All parties involved, Ron Costa, Tiga & Audion have all made the process of getting this record out to the people & now it's here & I hope people like it! :)

Inspired by the liberating seduction of house music in the 80’s, italian producer, DJ & artist Andrea Arcangeli is definitely a sound institute & technical virtuoso, presenting his “Blade Of Grass“ Ep, OFF119.
Incipient with subtly uplifting bassline, the title track “Blade Of Grass“ creates a big sense of tension, while wavy vocals surround the differing layers of Arcangeli’s first soundspace-strike.
Second track, “Sun Black“, contains a lighter Bass & rhythmic-structure, but catches everyone’s perception through its neat melody. A track full of atmosphere.
In a final step Pacifica, especially known for their Drumpoet Community Release & our Core Artists Melokolektiv take hand in remixing the grand originals.

tracks.tag_list: "Light Year" Exploited Deep House TechHouse "Feeling This Way" Berlin
tracks.title: Light Year - Feeling This Way | Exploited
tracks.description:
Early support by Loco Dice, Tiga, Boys Noize, Erol Alkan, Audiojack, XXXY, dOP, Ossie, Miguel Campbell, Danny Howard/BBC Radio1, Kiki...

UK-based Australian Light Year’s last record ’Never Know’ on Exploited had ’strains of chill wave and witch house, with looped, distant vocal snippets and a breezy vibe. Since his release on Spectral Sound the former electro house producer was saying hello to L.I.E.S, Trilogy Tapes and more straightforward house and techno.’ (Resident Advisor) 
While his first releases were leaning on the more melodic side ’Feeling This Way’ (his follow-up on Exploited) is more functional and stripped down just to the bare essentials - a drum track and a vocal snippet - pretty much influenced by some of the Ghetto House records he was listening to when he did this track. ’Slow Burn’ on the other hand is a collaboration with Jas Shaw from Simian Mobile Disco. Jas had just sourced some new pieces of kit for the SMD live album concept they were working on. They used a Cirklin sequencer - one of the most intuitive analogue sequencers you could probably use. The track pretty much wrote itself once they sequenced their modular synthesizer. The final version was created, produced and mixed in that one session. We hope you enjoy these 2 infectious tracks as much as we do. 

Label: Exploited
Artist: Light Year
Release: Feeling This Way

tracks.tag_list: "James Silk" "Can't Wait" Exploited "Shir Khan" "Black Jukebox" Disco House Jam
tracks.title: James Silk - Can't Wait | Exploited
tracks.description:
Shir Khan and the illusive Exploited crew reveal the first compilation of the cultishly adored Black Jukebox series. It includes the sunniest grooves you’ve heard this year. ’Shir Khan Presents Black Jukebox Disco Jam 01’ is a soundsystem-ready disco-house jam which tickles the subwoofers beautifully and seems purpose built for eyes-wide-shut Summer terrace play in big outdoor spaces. Black Jukebox is traversing the wide spectrum of ‘dancefloor’ music.  There’s much to excite: All four tracks are built for rooftop parties with the deep V crew.
From slo-mo housed up boogie-soul, to a loft-party future classic, to a feel-good, sun-blushed, druggy, late night electric jam, to main room filtered disco house and subbass-bugged R&B…it’s all there.  It’s no wonder the Black Jukebox Vinyl series became buy-on-sight and quick to disappear. Launched in late 2011 by Shir Khan, Black Jukebox was mainly focussed on Vinyl Releases. 13 Releases later, this is the first compilation which sums up some of the best moments and features 3 tracks that were digitally never available before. 
Black Jukebox Releases have put a smile on the face of various tastemakers such as Wolf&Lamb, Soul Clap, Tim Sweeney, Optimo, Axel Boman, Gerd Janson, Disclosure, Danny Krivit, Ewan Pearson, David August, Jesse Rose, Tiefschwarz, Matthew Dear, A-Trak, Huxley, Oliver $, Wareika, RubnTug, ND Baumecker, Acid Pauli, James Friedman, Mano Le Tough, Solomun, H.O.S.H., Daniel Bortz, Dyed Soundorom, Erol Alkan, Totally Enormous Extinct Dinosaurs, Deetron, Skream, Seth Troxler, Re.You, Keinemusik, Noir, Miss Kittin, Joakim, Munk, DJ Yoda, Hot Since 82, Pete Tong, Claptone, Karmon, Azari & III, Friendly Fires, Jazzanova, Drop Out Orchestra, El Txef, Maya Jane Coles, Till Von Sein, The Rapture, Peter Kruder, Arthur Baker, Miguel Campbell, Phil Weeks, Lee Foss, Maxxi Soundsystem, Luke Solomon, Mark Farina, Terranova, Pen Pearce, Acid Washed.

tracks.tag_list: VONSTROKE Justin Jay House "Tech House" "Deep House"
tracks.title: Justin Jay - Hit It [PREMIERE]
tracks.description:
Justin Jay - Mom, I Graduated!

BUY:
Beatport: http://j.mp/MomIGraduated
iTunes: http://smarturl.it/MomIGraduated
Spotify: http://spoti.fi/1JsSIaY


From the heat of the BBQ to the smoking hot talent of Justin Jay, as he returns to the feathery fold with his latest release. The youngest of VonStroke's proteges, the 22 year old producer continues to build on the promise shown on a string of heavy hitting Dirtybird releases (Femme Fatale, Static, Instincts, Le Voyou.)  With all of his tracks created on the same college-dorm studio set up, it seems fitting that we bring you the last from those late night bunker sessions and a brace dedicated to the end of his studies and the start of the party.

'Mom I Graduated' launches in to life with the sassily titled ‘Hit It.’  Spring loaded beats adorn an eerie, vocoder-aided atmosphere, before double claps on the beat turn the track into an intensified stomper. The drop descends into thick sub bass, chopped up vocal samples and chiming, echoing percussion around its half time rhythm. This is big!!

Rain Dance starts life out of earshot.  A progressive melodic flurry gradually enters in to range through a mist of pitter patter FX touches, while ascending woodblocks bring us to the vocal drop and a thumping kick drum -“I’m gonna make it rain” - Booty aesthetics with a slowed tribal rhythm and swathes of sub bass leak through the speakers. A second summer anthem from the young Californian.

tracks.title: Moon Boots - Red Sky (Medlar Remix)
tracks.description:
Buy/Stream: https://Anjunadeep.lnk.to/RedSkyRemixes
Release Date: 26th February 2016

US house sensation Moon Boots made his Anjunadeep debut late last year with the soulful throwback grooves of ‘Red Sky’, which picked up big support from Annie Mac on BBC Radio 1, Jason Bentley on KCRW and from a host of tastemaker DJs including Gorgon City, Tiga and Claude VonStroke. Two UK talents now step up for remix duties – Medlar and Kahwe.

Medlar has previously remixed Disclosure, Groove Armada and Tensnake, and put out a string of gorgeous EPs on Wolf Music. He ups the ante on his remix, blending the original melodies with dark bassline and punchy percussion.

Kahwe brings his own unique style to proceedings, delivering a mellow take full of atmospheric live percussion, warm fuzzy basslines and cascading melodies.

tracks.tag_list: Jeudi Monte "Data Transmission" "Debut Transmission"
tracks.title: Monte - Radical
tracks.description:
As you may have guessed by our extensive coverage of all things Jeudi, we're quite the fans of Doctor Dru's imprint here at Data Transmission, with the outlet quickly becoming one of favourite labels in recent times. For the Hamburg outpost's latest trick, they welcome back Monte, who – you might well recall – impressed upon on the label with a number of releases that arrived to to great fanfare last year and thanks to the glorious sounds of the 'Radical' EP, we’re delighted to announce that the man behind the music has lost none of his nous in the intervening time.

The action gets underway thanks to title track and our choice for premiere, ‘Radical’, a rollicking rollercoaster of a track aimed squarely at peak time dance floors which motors along to give clubbers something to really sink their teeth into. Slickly driven synth lines underpin a sparse yet menacing vocal line full of promise, with the track heaving along as it flexes its production prowess for a cut sure to be finding its way into the sets of house music's more discerning selectors upon release. Backed by a remix from Man Power and frenetic B-side 'Simpler', which jam packed with off kilter energy, is similarly sure to pick up plenty of attention during the small hours in the coming months and add a spine-tingling sense of drama to any set it pervades.

Set to arrive November 2nd, you can stream 'Radical' in full now. Enjoy.

As we get ready for a busy summer, of spreading the sound of tomorrow across the globe, we can't help but take a step back and bring you all the feel good, forward thinking music you know and love from Soulection. This installment of our White Label series comes from 18 year old London composer, songwriter, guitarist, singer & violinist, Tom Misch. We felt the need to list all of this in the description, because each track is such an audio masterpiece. This one is for everyone, but true fans of Dilla, and smooth, mellow, R&B inspired hip-hop beats, will definitely enjoy this release.

"Basically this EP is me attempting to make instrumentals that will effect people moods in a positive way but also make people think, all produced and recorded by myself in my bedroom. iTunes: Smarturl.it/NoReasonRemixes
Subscribe to Fool's Gold! smarturl.it/FGTV

From Outside Lands to iPhone ads, Giraffage is everywhere. His debut Fool’s Gold EP No Reason WiFi’ed glistening melodies and candy-painted basslines direct to your heart. Now it’s time for the new No Reason Remixes to get to work on the rest of your body, thanks to reconfigured versions from some of the coolest and most inventive names in dance and electronic music. GTA, Shash’U, Lindsay Lowend, Promnite, Maxo, Spazzkid and Qrion all put their spin on No Reason originals, pinballing from heavy-duty festival jams and club-ready explosions to juked out video game soundtracks and full-on IDM instrumentals. The matrix has never been this live!

tracks.description:
Watch the official video: https://youtube.com/watch?v=3Hv1DElPXV0
Download: http://smarturl.it/GiraffageEP

Giraffage's signature remixes of R&B favorites quickly took him from blogs to Boiler Room and beyond, as he won over dancefloors worldwide with lush, bass-driven sets. No Reason marks another new turning point for this artist, who has grown from flipping Janet Jackson songs to crafting indelible slow jams of his own. The chopped vocals and bubble wrap riffs of "Tell Me" combine for a Tumblr-era love ballad like none other, and the entire EP is as heartfelt as it is head-nodding.

Purchase "No Reason" on iTunes now: smarturl.it/GiraffageEP

tracks.title: Christina Perri - Burning Gold (Autograf Remix)
tracks.description:
Like the track? Click the [↻ Repost] button!

Buy link: http://found.ee/XDdYF

For us, the beauty about the Future is the endless possibilities it holds. In essence, it's a blank canvas waiting to be painted on. We'd love nothing more than to 'build' and 'make' a Future that's all our own. That means doing everything ourselves from scratch, bringing the hand of the artist back. So as we've been building a studio in the backyard and working on our live show, we wanted to start this new "Future Nites" series of remixes and originals with an eye on creating music for these live performances. We added a marimba to the live set, and can't wait to get some more analog gear into the studio so we can take these Future Beats to the next level.

It's been a fun ride for us putting all our heart and soul into this new project, so we hope this song takes you on an equally epic journey. As summer turns to fall, and day turns to night, we hope that you'll paint these empty canvases of endless possibilities with us. You do it by sharing and blasting music out into the world, with every action you make. It's about leaving your mark on the world. It's about leaving your Autograf. This is Future Nites.

As we get ready for a busy summer, of spreading the sound of tomorrow across the globe, we can't help but take a step back and bring you all the feel good, forward thinking music you know and love from Soulection. tracks.tag_list: Electronic
tracks.title: Lane 8 - Ghost ft. Patrick Baker (Lane 8 Rework)
tracks.description:
Beatport: po.st/GhostRemixes
Release Date: 18th May 2015

Rising Anjunadeep star Lane 8 announced the release of his debut album in style recently, with the brilliant new single ‘Ghost feat. Patrick Baker’. On remix duties are a diverse trio of talented producers; techno innovator Audion, Aus Music prodigy Bwana and blogger's favourite Luvian.

After collaborating with Lane 8 on a track on the upcoming album, Matthew Dear took to his notorious Audion guise to remix ‘Ghost’, following remixes for legendary acts like Leftfield, Four Tet, Dubfire and Seth Troxler. Completely twisting the mood of the original, cutting the vocal over a frenetic groove he delivers a gnarly late-night techno cut.

Bwana has marked himself out as one to watch with his excellent EPs on Will Saul’s Aus Music, and his epic take on ‘Ghost’ is another winner, playing off the subtle melodies of the original with a huge bass hook, and Patrick Baker’s evocative lyrics.

UK based Luvian has been bubbling away for a while, with his early tracks picking up millions of plays on YouTube and Soundcloud. He takes his remix away from the club, instead opting for a gorgeous poolside version, stripping back almost entirely to sparse percussion, sensual melodic textures and warped vocals.

tracks.tag_list: CamelPhat "Siren Song" Eden Axwell
tracks.title: CamelPhat feat. Eden - Siren Song
tracks.description:
Out now!!
http://axtone.co/SirenSong 
http://axtone.co/SirenSongiT
http://axtone.co/AxtoneSpotify

Continually emphasising its commitment to quality music, regardless of genres, Axtone Records is pleased to welcome back UK house duo CamelPhat to the label for their summer single, ‘Siren Song’. Premiered via festival-behemoth Tomorrowland, CamelPhat demonstrate their appreciation for the softer side of house music, choosing to intertwine warm vocals and melodies with their consistently sleek production.

CamelPhat have been busy throughout 2015 with singles such as ‘Paradigm’ (Axtone Records) and ‘Constellations’ (Spinnin’ Records) both garnering heavy BBC Radio 1 support. Following an EP on Great Stuff Recordings, ‘Constellations’ has impacted both the Top 10 and Deep House charts of Beatport, quickly making CamelPhat into some of the UK’s most in demand producers.

With musical influences rooted in RnB and Motown, UK-based singer and songwriter, Eden is well versed in the world of dance having numerous releases on Fedde Le Grand’s Flamingo Records.

In an era of loud noises and big kicks, ‘Siren Song’ upholds Axtone’s belief that quality production and emotional substance will always shine through...

tracks.tag_list: Compuphonic "Marques Toliver" "The Sun Does Rise" Exploited House Deep Berlin
tracks.title: Compuphonic - The Sun Does Rise feat. Marques Toliver | Exploited
tracks.description:
Featured as Belgian artist of the moment in DJ Mag Belgium Issue.
Premiered on Majestic Casual Youtube Channel with over 200 000 Plays in 1 week.

Mixmag: 'With Florida singer Marques Toliver's smooth as silk vocals weaving in and out, Compuphonic's layering of sprightly pads and deft snares make for yet another super lush house cut.'

Early support by BBC Radio 1/Danny Howard, Laurent Garnier, Robag Wruhme, DJ T, Tensnake, The Magician, Miguel Campbell, Karotte, Arthur Baker, Adana Twins, Agoria, Doctor Dru, Peter Kruder, Mickey, Kartell, Ruede Hagelstein, Lane 8 and many more.

Instrumentals and Radio Edits upon request: mail to info@exploitedghetto.de or leave feedback in comments if you require so.

Pre-Order ITunes:
http://bit.ly/CompuphonicMagicalShoes

With over 7 million plays and counting on YouTube Compuphonic's 2011 collaboration with Marques Toliver, 'Sunset' raised the bar pretty high. Since then Maxime has gone on to produce remixes for the likes of Giorgio Moroder, Gotye even and fellow Belgians The Subs (winning a Red Bull award in the process) and release two acclaimed EPs on Berlin label Exploited.

Now finally Maxime and Marques have reunited for a new EP on Exploited, 'Magical Shoes', and the results are everything we could have hoped for.

Having delivered two huge club hits in 2014 with ’Radio Atlantis’ and ’O Cypres’, Belgian star Compuphonic returns this February with his third EP for Exploited, ‘Magical Shoes’. 2 tracks of sublime House music, the ‘Magical Shoes’ EP sees Compuphonic finally reunited with the Beyoncé approved American singer Marques Toliver, whose vocals previously graced Maxime’s 2012 breakout hit ’Sunset’.

Once again this Transatlantic pairing have struck gold as Compuphonic’s distinctive brand of deeply emotional, nuanced, House Music provides the perfect setting for Marques’ plaintive vocals. With it’s distinctive Korg M1 organ and shuffling beats ‘Magical Shoes’ instantly brings to mind legendary ‘90s New York clubs like The Sound Factory but thanks to Compuphonic’s production skills it goes well beyond that of simple period pastiche and sounds utterly fresh for 2015, a bonafide club hit that is already peppering the sets of DJs such as Laurent Garnier, Tensnake and The Magician.

As the title suggests the EP’s 2nd track ‘The Sun Does Rise’ is the natural successor to the duo’s previous outing. As deep as the Pacific Ocean this is a trance inducing hymn to hope, music designed to elevate the soul as much as move the body and bring some much needed warmth back to clubland. Expect to hear this played everywhere and anywhere this year where the party goes through the night and the first morning light breaks over the dancefloor.

Recorded in the famous Vantage Point Studios in Antwerp - dEUS’s own recording studio, a special, inspiring moment for Maxime, a lifelong fan of the band - the ‘Magical Shoes’ EP cements his position as one of Europe’s most talented producers and with remixes to come soon on Carl Craig’s Planet E and more original material on Exploited, the future is looking bright for Compuphonic.

tracks.tag_list: Sandrino Adriatique
tracks.title: Free Download: Frankey & Sandrino - Lost (Adriatique Mix)
tracks.description:
♫ Free Download ♫:
http://www.deephouseamsterdam.com/free-download-frankey-sandrino-lost-adriatique-remix

The basis of any great partnership is how one complements the other, which in the case of the Adrians, was evident from the outset.

While one had honed his musical chops with House for the US and Detroit Techno, the other dwelled in deep melodies and European techno. In the world of dance music, where producers might spend a few nights DJ’ing and some DJ's may dabble in producing, their partnership has mastered both while bridging the perspectives of two varied backgrounds bound by the ultimate desire to forge a unique sonic signature and connect with the audience that shares in their deeply held belief that music is meditation. Forging relationships with artists and labels that share in their sensibilities, Adriatique has released on Zurich's Cityfox, LA's Culprit, New York's Wolf & Lamb, London's Supernature, Canada’s My Favorite Robot and most frequently, Hamburg's Diynamic. 

Frankey and Sandrino, have been active with electronic music for well over a decade now. While Franky is a schooled musician who had already released a string of LP's and EP's, Sandrino started his career in 2003 with a residency at Germany's Butan Club. The duo of Frankey and Sandrino soon discovered their shared interest in deep and melodic music and started producing together. It didn't take too long until Four:Twenty Records and Moodmusic picked up their first releases.

Today we have a very special gift for you with a brand new track from Frankey and Sandrino, 'Lost,' featuring Adriatique on the remix duties. The track is an atmospheric and steady builder, with a distorted vocal and choppy bassline.

tracks.title: PREMIERE: Vincenzo - Melbs
tracks.description:
Taken from the EP 'Malvern Road' out on Friday, 19th: https://soundcloud.com/dessous-recordings/sets/vincenzo-malvern-road-ep

https://www.facebook.com/page.vincenzo
http://www.residentadvisor.net/dj/vincenzo
https://soundcloud.com/vincenzo_official


Full release info:

Superb deepness from a master of the genre. Vincenzo - a man that needs little introduction thanks to his tireless contribution to the house music scene via labels like Dessous, Poker Flat, Liebe*Detail, Winding Road, Beadrock, Anjunadeep, his own label Teardrop and many more - drops a brand new EP on the Dessous imprint.

Joined by Voyeurhythm chief Tyson Ballard for the title track, 'Malvern Road' is an epic 10 minute journey into space - drifting and evolving via acid squelches, pad washes and driven by a crisp, tight rhythm section.

'Follow' is a tougher proposition - adding a techy rumble and offset percussion to Vincenzo’s exceptional production.

'Melbs' is another groove-laden joint, built around a poly-rhythmic shuffle and deep, Detroit influenced chords, co-written and produced with Melbournian friend Mic Newman (also known as Fantastic Man for his releases on Fine Choice).

For the Beatport release 'Such Great Heights' completes this impressive release - a slow building intro leads into a euphoric, punchy jam for the floor.

Traxsource co-founder Brian Tappert provides a live edit of 'Malvern Road'.

tracks.tag_list: "Jody Wisternoff" "Lane 8" Anjunadeep
tracks.title: Lane 8 - Sunlight (Jody Wisternoff Remix)
tracks.description:
Release Date: 11th March 2016

With the release of his debut artist album ‘Rise’ on Anjunadeep last summer Lane 8 aka Daniel Goldstein established himself as one of the electronic scene’s most exciting talents, warranting a stream of support from international tastemakers including Pete Tong, Jason Bentley and Annie Mac along with glowing coverage from The New York Times, Mixmag and The Fader. 

Lane 8 follows with a collection of high calibre remixes from a host of talented producers, along with new mixes from Anjunadeep stalwart Jody Wisternoff, emerging British talent Theo Kottis, as well as his own rework of album opener ‘Loving You’.

Lane 8’s rework of 'Loving You’ twists the vocal finesse of Lulu James into a brooding tech-house roller that explores the darker side of Goldstein’s production; an undeniable dance floor weapon. Fresh off the heels of his Anjunadeep debut ‘Into The Wild’, Theo Kottis takes to the stage again with an atmospheric down-tempo remix of melodic gem ‘Klara’.

Jody Wisternoff offers a hallmark uplifting remix of vocal track ‘Sunlight’. Wisternoff layers a punchy bassline groove with mellow synths beneath the summery topline. Further remixes come from some of the scenes most in demand names, including Audion (aka Matthew Dear), Moon Boots, Kiwi, Yotto and Bwana.

tracks.tag_list: "Doctor Dru" "Adana Twins" "Juicy Fruit" Exploited "Shir Khan" "Black Jukebox" Disco House Jam
tracks.title: Doctor Dru & Adana Twins - Juicy Fruit | Exploited
tracks.description:
Shir Khan and the illusive Exploited crew reveal the first compilation of the cultishly adored Black Jukebox series. It includes the sunniest grooves you’ve heard this year. ’Shir Khan Presents Black Jukebox Disco Jam 01’ is a soundsystem-ready disco-house jam which tickles the subwoofers beautifully and seems purpose built for eyes-wide-shut Summer terrace play in big outdoor spaces. Black Jukebox is traversing the wide spectrum of ‘dancefloor’ music.  There’s much to excite: All four tracks are built for rooftop parties with the deep V crew.
From slo-mo housed up boogie-soul, to a loft-party future classic, to a feel-good, sun-blushed, druggy, late night electric jam, to main room filtered disco house and subbass-bugged R&B…it’s all there.  It’s no wonder the Black Jukebox Vinyl series became buy-on-sight and quick to disappear. Launched in late 2011 by Shir Khan, Black Jukebox was mainly focussed on Vinyl Releases. 13 Releases later, this is the first compilation which sums up some of the best moments and features 3 tracks that were digitally never available before. 
Black Jukebox Releases have put a smile on the face of various tastemakers such as Wolf&Lamb, Soul Clap, Tim Sweeney, Optimo, Axel Boman, Gerd Janson, Disclosure, Danny Krivit, Ewan Pearson, David August, Jesse Rose, Tiefschwarz, Matthew Dear, A-Trak, Huxley, Oliver $, Wareika, RubnTug, ND Baumecker, Acid Pauli, James Friedman, Mano Le Tough, Solomun, H.O.S.H., Daniel Bortz, Dyed Soundorom, Erol Alkan, Totally Enormous Extinct Dinosaurs, Deetron, Skream, Seth Troxler, Re.You, Keinemusik, Noir, Miss Kittin, Joakim, Munk, DJ Yoda, Hot Since 82, Pete Tong, Claptone, Karmon, Azari & III, Friendly Fires, Jazzanova, Drop Out Orchestra, El Txef, Maya Jane Coles, Till Von Sein, The Rapture, Peter Kruder, Arthur Baker, Miguel Campbell, Phil Weeks, Lee Foss, Maxxi Soundsystem, Luke Solomon, Mark Farina, Terranova, Pen Pearce, Acid Washed.

tracks.title: Prommer & Barck | The Barking Grizzle (Detroit / Berlin) (San Soda Remix)
tracks.description:
These are stripped down versions of the original tracks !!!

Tracklisting:
Side A: 
1. Journey (KiNK Remix) (08:02) 
 
Side AA: 
1. The Barking Grizzle (Detroit-Berlin) (Norman & Jerome Sydenham Remix) (9:16) 
2. The Barking Grizzle (San Soda Remix) (5:46) 
 
Digital Bonustrack: 
Journey (KiNK Dub) (8:04) 

Taking the next level, the infectious grooves and fiercely beauteousness of the highly acclaimed Prommer & Barck album „Alex & The Grizzly“ are mesmerized here any further. KiNK , San Soda and Norman & Jerome Sydenham captivating the journey into the variety of idiosyncratic house music.  
 
KiNK’s coproduction with a various number of esteemed DJs and producers, like Laurent Garnier or Macro’s head Stefan Goldmann, Bulgarian-based KINK gained a certain status in the underground dance music scene. His innovative style of producing jumps between house grooves and experimental electronica with an acid connotation, gained in releases on such diverging labels like Cocoon, Liebe Detail, Ovum or Permanent Vacation, next to others. Whilst producing dance music he pushes the Bulgarian pop scene as well. Other artists he worked with: 
Neville Watson (the collaboration track “Inside Out” it landed at Steve Bug`s prestigious “Bugnology vol. 3” mix compilation), DJ Sneak, DJ Rolando, Osunlade, James Ruskin, Ken Ishii, Llorca, Funk D’Void, Terrence Dixon, Samuel L Session, Paul Woolford, Chris Duckenfield, or Crookers.  
 
Thanks to his refreshing sound Belgium-based San Soda managed to become quite a name in the international house scene. Just take his several 12“ releases on Red D’s We Play House-Label and you will discover nothing but well produced bubbly deep house, soulful techno or sounds that just smoothly waft in between. His critical 
acclaimed LP „Immers & Daarentegen“ defines his diverse style, which coexists in an emotional, yet intoxicating way. 
 
Norman is Norman Methner, one of the most passionated entrepeneurs in Berlin (he used to work for Hell’s Gigolo), nowadays the head honcho soul behind the Cookies club. He graciously teamed up with Ibadan legend Jerome Sydenham to produce a powerful remix of a track, which both liked so much.

tracks.tag_list: "Bukka & Molinari" "Mind Games" Exploited "Black Jukebox" "Shir Khan" Disco House Jam
tracks.title: Bukka & Molinari - Mind Games | Exploited
tracks.description:
Shir Khan and the illusive Exploited crew reveal the first compilation of the cultishly adored Black Jukebox series. It includes the sunniest grooves you’ve heard this year. ’Shir Khan Presents Black Jukebox Disco Jam 01’ is a soundsystem-ready disco-house jam which tickles the subwoofers beautifully and seems purpose built for eyes-wide-shut Summer terrace play in big outdoor spaces. Black Jukebox is traversing the wide spectrum of ‘dancefloor’ music.  There’s much to excite: All four tracks are built for rooftop parties with the deep V crew.
From slo-mo housed up boogie-soul, to a loft-party future classic, to a feel-good, sun-blushed, druggy, late night electric jam, to main room filtered disco house and subbass-bugged R&B…it’s all there.  It’s no wonder the Black Jukebox Vinyl series became buy-on-sight and quick to disappear. Launched in late 2011 by Shir Khan, Black Jukebox was mainly focussed on Vinyl Releases. 13 Releases later, this is the first compilation which sums up some of the best moments and features 3 tracks that were digitally never available before. 
Black Jukebox Releases have put a smile on the face of various tastemakers such as Wolf&Lamb, Soul Clap, Tim Sweeney, Optimo, Axel Boman, Gerd Janson, Disclosure, Danny Krivit, Ewan Pearson, David August, Jesse Rose, Tiefschwarz, Matthew Dear, A-Trak, Huxley, Oliver $, Wareika, RubnTug, ND Baumecker, Acid Pauli, James Friedman, Mano Le Tough, Solomun, H.O.S.H., Daniel Bortz, Dyed Soundorom, Erol Alkan, Totally Enormous Extinct Dinosaurs, Deetron, Skream, Seth Troxler, Re.You, Keinemusik, Noir, Miss Kittin, Joakim, Munk, DJ Yoda, Hot Since 82, Pete Tong, Claptone, Karmon, Azari & III, Friendly Fires, Jazzanova, Drop Out Orchestra, El Txef, Maya Jane Coles, Till Von Sein, The Rapture, Peter Kruder, Arthur Baker, Miguel Campbell, Phil Weeks, Lee Foss, Maxxi Soundsystem, Luke Solomon, Mark Farina, Terranova, Pen Pearce, Acid Washed.

tracks.title: Fingerprint
tracks.description:
We live at a time when distractions from reality are never further away than our fingertips. Our phones offer us unlimited stimulation and temporary comfort. The possibilities of technology are endless, but they also limit the possibility…the possibility to truly experience and submit to the moment.

For me, going to a club has always been about letting go of the world around me, like a vacation from the nagging realities of everyday life. In the best clubs I have been to, the people were united by a desire to experience electronic music in the purest sense; to get lost in its tension and release. No matter what was going on in their lives, it was a place where, for at least a few hours, nothing else mattered but the sheer power music had to bring people joy. And those experiences - held only by those in that room, at that moment - were almost like the reward to submitting to a secret society. At the end of the night, I could look at my friends, old and new, and without saying a single word, we'd know that what we experienced together was something special, something that would never quite be repeated again.

Some of my early clubbing experiences have stayed with me for my entire life. They are why I'm doing what I'm doing today. There is not a photo, forum thread or social media post in existence to mark their happening, but the memories, the emotions I felt, the way those nights changed my life - those things stay with me to this day.

Somewhere along the way, we as a society have lost the ability to experience those special moments. On the rare occasion that they do happen, we scramble to grab our phones in time to capture them - but those moments cannot be truly captured - and they don’t need to be broadcasted or recorded. Sometimes, the best thing we can do is fully appreciate what is happening in that room, at that moment, with those people around us. 

I think our society needs clubbing experiences where they go home with more than just a picture to post on instagram. That's why I'm starting This Never Happened - I want to create that experience for people.

At This Never Happened, we invite you into a space where the only thing that matters are the people in that room, the music and the magic that happens when those things interact. An event where the dancefloor will be a phone and photo-free space.

This experience we share together may, by 2016 standards, have never happened. But those who dare will always know - something special did happen here. 

The first show will be a return to my hometown of San Francisco on 3 June at Mezzanine. It's a venue I've dreamed of headlining for many years and the perfect place to start this new chapter. If we can make this happen - and work - together, there will be many, many more. 

This Never Happened will not just be the name of these events, but also the name of a new record label. This label will be the outlet for music, by me, that is inspired by and made for this experience. The first song I'm releasing is called "Fingerprint" and you can listen to it below.

Putting this project together with my team over the last 6 months triggered a creative spark in me unlike anything I've ever felt before, and I'm so excited for you guys to hear the music I've come up with during that time.

I look forward to building this concept with you :)

Love,
Daniel

tracks.title: Premiere: Catz 'N Dogz - Czas Poczeka (Chyba) (Fred Everything Remix)
tracks.description:
♫ More ♫
http://www.deephouseamsterdam.com/premiere-catz-n-dogz-czas-poczeka-chyba-fred-everything-remix/
Fresh from Catz ‘N Dogz own recent remixes of Disclosure, Roisin Murphy and Rufus comes their own remix compilation of their Basic Colour Theory album from artists such as Fred Everything, Jamie Jones, Claude Von Stroke, Eats Everything, Jay Shepheard, and Skudge.

The original cuts of the Polish duo's third full-length Basic Colour Theory combined traditional songwriting and the group’s signature bass lines. This was undoubtedly influenced by the group’s busy DJ schedules around the world. The duo invited a number of guest vocalists to contribute to the project, including Green Velvet and Phat Kat.

Across the weighty 16 tracks on the full release are warm grooves and up-tempo cuts. Each remix itself demands attention, as each one blissfully captures the original's fun-based lovingness. Other highlights featured on the compilation album such as Good Touch, Get It Right and The Joy are equally bulkier in vibe, more expansive, yet often less capacious in detail. 

Premiering here on DHA is the remix by UK based DJ/Remixer/Producer Fred Everything. The remix is thought of as an extended method of quotation, citation and commentary with each new sound enforcing the consistency and dependability of Catz ‘N Dogz original production, as melodies and vocals are trimmed away in favor of reimagined newfound rhythms.

The collection will be released digitally as well as on vinyl on 11th March 2016.

tracks.title: Cubicolor - Next Planet
tracks.description:
Beatport: http://bit.ly/bp-next-planet
iTunes: http://bit.ly/next-planet-ep

Making their debut on Anjunadeep with their first ever release are Cubicolor - an emerging act from the Netherlands with an exciting flair for melody, and an impressive command of deep house grooves. 
 
Title track "Next Planet" was an instant favourite with the label A&R team, skilfully building a slow-burning epic from a simple, repetitive riff, accompanied by brooding melodic flourishes and stirring climactic pads.
 
"Soul Chords" showcases a more laid-back side to Cubicolor's sound, incorporating jazz and funk influences as chugging grooves and a wandering bassline are paired up with dreamy atmospherics. Perfect poolside material.
 
Again highlighting their deft touch, "New Roads" grows from subtle beginnings into a deep sun-kissed gem, guided by rolling low-end and infectious piano stabs.

⚡⚡⚡ (◔◡◔) click [ ↻ repost ] & [ ♥ like ] button, if you like it ⚡⚡⚡


After their power-loaded single “Sugar” the Austrian duo Wild Culture is back with their new track “Nervous”. Together with US singer and songwriter Dan Mackenzie they crossed the deep house borders with a soulful piano and R&B rhythm including their typical electronic and nature-intensive elements. Mackenzie’s vocals are smoothly surrounded in a very warm and individual way to bring along the perfect summer vibe. Wild Culture is once again convincing with incredible diversity in their music repertoire and happy to make their listeners fall into a very chill but also dancy mood.

tracks.tag_list: Nicolas Jaar Clown and Sunset Love You Gotta Lose Again
tracks.title: Nicolas Jaar - Love You Gotta Lose Again
tracks.description: Inés' LP is home to some of Jaar's most eclectic and wonderful recordings. This project is a personal quest of which he holds full control, introducing some young and gifted voices from far-flung corners of the globe. Sold in the rare format of a USB necklace as well as digital, Inès' is brought to the world on his own flourishing Clown & Sunset label, which has since only released a small amount of productions. The LP has an organic nature with hints of mysticism within its rumbling textures. Ripe with sentiment, Inés' has an innate hunger to challenge the view that electronic music is void of emotion. This collection is an accessible and pioneering take on contemporary electronic music, from the fizzing embers of Jaar's Dubliners' to the jagged reverberations of Nikita Quasim's Freshmen Year' and the raw harmonies of Soul Keita's Dusties N 808s'. A fearless and intuitive voice forms through the LP, concocting a fresh light into what lies within Jaar's musical universe.

tracks.title: Bassmelodie | La Despedida
tracks.description:
Every single end also is at the same time a new beginning. 

We're gonna move to South America in a couple of days and since today it is also my birthday, I thought it would be a perfect opportunity to give away my new mixtape which I named (matching to our situation) "La Despedida" (farewell).
I included some very emotional tracks in this set and I hope that every single person out there who is gonna listen to my farewell gift is also able to feel what I'm trying to convey...

Of course my project will keep going the only difference will be that in the future I will have another post address and a new environment that hopefully will be influencing my creativity in a positive way. Most likely I might also shed some tears but heaven knows we never need to be ashamed of our tears, for they are rain upon the blinding dust of earth, overlying our hard hearts. 

Love,
BM

tracks.tag_list: "Kerrier District" Hypercolour "Boiler Room Debuts"
tracks.title: Kerrier District "Techno Disco (KiNK Remix)" - Boiler Room Debuts
tracks.description:
Last year's '4' album saw Mr. Luke Vibert's first venture as Kerrier District in over a decade. And a successful venture it was at that – with the album becoming into an essential long player, and ranking as one of Bleep's top albums of 2015, Now, to mark Hypercolour's 50th single release, four of electronic music's heavyweights have brought forward three strong reworkings of 4: Ricardo Villalobos & Max Loderbauer, Head High (aka Shed) and RA Best Live Act of 2015, KiNK – whose remix comes up trumps in our eyes.

In his take on album favourite, "Techno Disco", KiNK deploys a spacey synth melody and a Reese-style bassline – transforming it into an energetic peaktime track, with elements not falling sonically far from a UR record.

tracks.tag_list: Anjunadeep House Deep Cubicolor "Got This Feeling" "Still Linger In My Dreams" "A New High" Techno
tracks.title: Cubicolor - Got This Feeling
tracks.description:
Pre-order Anjunadeep 07: http://po.st/Anjunadeep07
Beatport - http://po.st/bgotthisfeeling
iTunes - http://po.st/igotthisfeeling
Spotify - http://po.st/sgotthisfeeling

Announcing themselves earlier this year with the “Next Planet EP", the mysterious Cubicolor are rapidly making a name for themselves. Pete Tong named them as one of the hottest acts to watch in the next 12 months, and the “Got This Feeling EP” shows exactly why.

Featured on Anjunadeep 06, title track “Got This Feeling” is an anthem in the best sense of the word; catchy but classy with intricate details. A chugging melodic groove and lazy percussion make way for a majestic piano breakdown and a joyous vocal loop. Anjuna regulars can finally put an ID to this one after hearing it on their Anjunadeep Edition mix earlier this year!

“Still Linger In My Dreams” is another beautiful piece of soulful and melodic dance music that shows Cubicolor at their most cinematic. Sweeping percussion combines with another gorgeous vocal loop, surrounded by deft textures and intricate production.

“A New High” sees Cubicolor show off their darker side, with a dancefloor orientated tech house weapon heard recently in Dom Donnelly’s Anjunadeep Edition mix. Energetic percussion drives the track through to a complex breakdown which builds and builds before skilfully dropping back into the flowing bass groove.

tracks.tag_list: "Pleasure State" "Anabel Englund" MK "Lee Foss"
tracks.title: HOTC053 Pleasure State -  Ghost In The System (FULL LENGTH PREVIEW)
tracks.description:
http://www.facebook.com/pleasurestatemusic
http://www.twitter.com/plsrstate
http://instagram.com/pleasurestatemusic
http://www.soundcloud.com/pleasurestatemusic

After debuting for the first time at this year’s We Are FSTVL, producers/DJs MK & Lee Foss and singer/songwriter Anabel Englund have announced their first official release together as Pleasure State. Coming out on Jamie Jones’ and Lee Foss’ label Hot Creations, the group announce the highly anticipated release of 'Ghost In The System’ on December 1st.

Pleasure State is a project driven by the group’s unusual implosive chemistry along with a vision to create melodic and impassioned house music. Their style is dark and sensual with haunting vocals, pulsing beats and uncensored subject matters. Successful in their own right, MK, Lee and Anabel bring a wealth of talent, experience and creativity to this new and exciting group and Pleasure State acts as a natural extension of who they are as individuals.

After Lee Foss met the intriguing Californian talent Anabel Englund, he brought her into his existing collaboration with house heavyweight MK, literally igniting sparks between the group, whose union was formalised with the stand-out track 'Electricity' for Hot Creations.  Pleasure State have carved out the time all over the world to get together and create, and they have now delivered this exceptional EP.

The evocative ‘Ghost In The System’ is inhabited by a sinister presence created by Anabel’s chilling vocal which is accompanied by a bouncing bass and distorted rap and the result in a full on haunting of an atmospheric dance track. The EP features the politically charged and hip-hop influenced dance record ’Subject Matter’ and a 12 minute remix of ‘Electricity’ from Detroit techno legend and Grammy award winner, Carl Craig.

Out for release through Ultra Music on April 1st is the richly melodic Lulleaux remix of Claire Guerreso’s ‘Skipping Stones. Having just only recently remixed Benny Benassi and Vassy’s ‘Even If’, the Dutch producer again shows serious studio skills with this month’s offering. 

With Guerreso’s original single still proving a huge success, Lulleaux puts his own uplifting slant on it, keeping those dreamy vocals as a focal point and creating additional texture from dynamic piano chords and a sharply pulsing beat beneath. 

With Lulleaux’s name continuing to spread through the scene like wildfire thanks to his sophisticated sound, it’s clear his ‘Skipping Stones’ edit will only emphasise this fact.

tracks.tag_list: "Patryk Molinari" "No Dilemma" Exploited "Shir Khan" "Black Jukebox" Disco House Jam
tracks.title: Patryk Molinari - No Dilemma | Exploited
tracks.description:
Shir Khan and the illusive Exploited crew reveal the first compilation of the cultishly adored Black Jukebox series. It includes the sunniest grooves you’ve heard this year. ’Shir Khan Presents Black Jukebox Disco Jam 01’ is a soundsystem-ready disco-house jam which tickles the subwoofers beautifully and seems purpose built for eyes-wide-shut Summer terrace play in big outdoor spaces. Black Jukebox is traversing the wide spectrum of ‘dancefloor’ music.  There’s much to excite: All four tracks are built for rooftop parties with the deep V crew.
From slo-mo housed up boogie-soul, to a loft-party future classic, to a feel-good, sun-blushed, druggy, late night electric jam, to main room filtered disco house and subbass-bugged R&B…it’s all there.  It’s no wonder the Black Jukebox Vinyl series became buy-on-sight and quick to disappear. Launched in late 2011 by Shir Khan, Black Jukebox was mainly focussed on Vinyl Releases. 13 Releases later, this is the first compilation which sums up some of the best moments and features 3 tracks that were digitally never available before. 
Black Jukebox Releases have put a smile on the face of various tastemakers such as Wolf&Lamb, Soul Clap, Tim Sweeney, Optimo, Axel Boman, Gerd Janson, Disclosure, Danny Krivit, Ewan Pearson, David August, Jesse Rose, Tiefschwarz, Matthew Dear, A-Trak, Huxley, Oliver $, Wareika, RubnTug, ND Baumecker, Acid Pauli, James Friedman, Mano Le Tough, Solomun, H.O.S.H., Daniel Bortz, Dyed Soundorom, Erol Alkan, Totally Enormous Extinct Dinosaurs, Deetron, Skream, Seth Troxler, Re.You, Keinemusik, Noir, Miss Kittin, Joakim, Munk, DJ Yoda, Hot Since 82, Pete Tong, Claptone, Karmon, Azari & III, Friendly Fires, Jazzanova, Drop Out Orchestra, El Txef, Maya Jane Coles, Till Von Sein, The Rapture, Peter Kruder, Arthur Baker, Miguel Campbell, Phil Weeks, Lee Foss, Maxxi Soundsystem, Luke Solomon, Mark Farina, Terranova, Pen Pearce, Acid Washed. 

Artist: Various Artists
Release: Shir Khan Presents Black Jukebox Disco Jam 01
Label: Exploited
Published by Exploited Ghetto Music Publishing

tracks.title: Onsra - Other Day | Exploited
tracks.description:
Liked by various cool cats such as Tanner Ross, Joakim, Claptone, I-Robots, Pete Herbert, Agoria, Chaim, XXXY, Quiet Village, Karotte, Fred Everything, Hector Moralez, Baikal, El Txef, Eli Escobar, Tensnake, Acid Pauli, Jaques Renault, Mark Farina, Inland Knights, Doctor Dru, Sinden, Phil Gerus, The Mekanism, Whitesquare, Compuphonic, Drop Out Orchestra...

It's the return of Black Jukebox.
300 Limited Vinyl Copies in store.
Sending out promos to those who like to put on their Disco Shoes.
P.S. We're looking for tracks for BJ16...

After a long hiatus Shir Khan hits us with the 14th edition featuring Onsra & Bas Roos. Secret Parisian project Onsra returns after killing it with "Funky Town" last year. First he gets down on the terrace with the loopy banger of "So Good". A 112BPM disco house number which has a touch of that old Soundstream magic about it yet is instantly, undeniably a Shir Khan favourite. When those string-led bridge sections burst into life you should see the whole terrace unite under some Vitamin D-laced pleasure. "Other Day" packs a bit more umph with tough boogie licks looped and chopped for more funky dancefloor goodness. Bas Roos takes over the flip and is a newbie youngster from Rotterdam with a fresh residency at Toffler Club keeping things bright, smooth and wide-eyed with "Searchin" and "Don’t Let Go The Disco". Both tracks epitomizing the feel-good spirit of classic funky house whilst still keeping the modern day nu-disco crowd happy. Shir Khan rides forth! Vinyl only, limited run. Move quick!

tracks.title: Fingerprint
tracks.description:
We live at a time when distractions from reality are never further away than our fingertips. Our phones offer us unlimited stimulation and temporary comfort. The possibilities of technology are endless, but they also limit the possibility…the possibility to truly experience and submit to the moment.

For me, going to a club has always been about letting go of the world around me, like a vacation from the nagging realities of everyday life. In the best clubs I have been to, the people were united by a desire to experience electronic music in the purest sense; to get lost in its tension and release. No matter what was going on in their lives, it was a place where, for at least a few hours, nothing else mattered but the sheer power music had to bring people joy. And those experiences - held only by those in that room, at that moment - were almost like the reward to submitting to a secret society. At the end of the night, I could look at my friends, old and new, and without saying a single word, we'd know that what we experienced together was something special, something that would never quite be repeated again.

Some of my early clubbing experiences have stayed with me for my entire life. They are why I'm doing what I'm doing today. There is not a photo, forum thread or social media post in existence to mark their happening, but the memories, the emotions I felt, the way those nights changed my life - those things stay with me to this day.

Somewhere along the way, we as a society have lost the ability to experience those special moments. On the rare occasion that they do happen, we scramble to grab our phones in time to capture them - but those moments cannot be truly captured - and they don’t need to be broadcasted or recorded. Sometimes, the best thing we can do is fully appreciate what is happening in that room, at that moment, with those people around us. 

I think our society needs clubbing experiences where they go home with more than just a picture to post on instagram. That's why I'm starting This Never Happened - I want to create that experience for people.

At This Never Happened, we invite you into a space where the only thing that matters are the people in that room, the music and the magic that happens when those things interact. An event where the dancefloor will be a phone and photo-free space.

This experience we share together may, by 2016 standards, have never happened. But those who dare will always know - something special did happen here. 

The first show will be a return to my hometown of San Francisco on 3 June at Mezzanine. It's a venue I've dreamed of headlining for many years and the perfect place to start this new chapter. If we can make this happen - and work - together, there will be many, many more. 

This Never Happened will not just be the name of these events, but also the name of a new record label. This label will be the outlet for music, by me, that is inspired by and made for this experience. The first song I'm releasing is called "Fingerprint" and you can listen to it below.

Putting this project together with my team over the last 6 months triggered a creative spark in me unlike anything I've ever felt before, and I'm so excited for you guys to hear the music I've come up with during that time.

I look forward to building this concept with you :)

Love,
Daniel

Like "French Kiss" or SIL's "Windows" from the 90s or Gorge's "Tayo" or "Rollox" by Adriatique from now, this is a gold-plated DJ weapon. For those looking for something a bit sassier, "No One Hears You" delivers a half-time-Superbowl of a track with loopy keys and bouncing bass. Lastly "The Quad" is the kind of simple-but-beautiful piano anthem that's perfect if you're in a simple-but-off-your-face kind of mood.

tracks.title: Denis Horvat - Apart (Hyenah Remix)
tracks.description:
There are few DJs and producers who have worked as hard for their success as Alex Niggemann. Gambling his future career on becoming a success story within the extremely competitive Berlin electronic music scene, this is a man who oozes confidence because he truly believes in what he is doing. No trend chasing, Alex has always tried to impress fans and critics alike with his eclectic tastes for music, ignoring genre boundaries whilst applying his relentless perfectionism to all of his projects across the sonic spectrum.

Thus it should come as little surprise that the latest EP from his now firmly established Aeon Audio imprint is an absolute belter. Welcoming back the talents of Croatian-born, Danish-bred Denis Horvat, the 'Apart' EP serves as another melodic milestone for the label as the fast rising producer turns in two club ready cuts sure to get the blood pumping this winter. It's Hyenah's remix of the record's title track that really set our pulses racing here at DT HQ though, the mysterious producer retaining the moody grooves of the original whilst using a brighter array of pads and stabs to lead his reinterpretation towards the light.

Set to arrive November 27th, we can assure you that you don't want to sleep on this one.

tracks.tag_list: "Tom Middleton" Vincenzo HEVA Anjunadeep
tracks.title: Tom Middleton - HEVA (Vincenzo Remix)
tracks.description:
Buy/Stream: https://Anjunadeep.lnk.to/HEVARemixes
Release Date: 20th May 2016

A true dance music pioneer, Tom Middleton has built up an impressive back catalogue over the past two decades including collaborations with the likes of Aphex Twin, Josh Wink, Adam Freehand, and notably with Mark Pritchard as Global Communication. That along with his solo prowess and memorable remixes for Kerri Chandler, Orbital, Ennio Morricone, Jon Hopkins and more have marked him out as one of the scene’s most respected artists.

2016 sees the return of Tom Middleton to Anjunadeep with a 4 track re-imagining of his 2015 club hit “HEVA”. The package features reworks from two diverse talents, Vincenzo and Geode, plus additional mixes from Tom himself including a stunning ambient production and 2-Step remix.

Both of Tom’s own EP contributions are trademark examples of his deft skill and ingenuity when reworking his own productions. Two diverse takes on an Anjuna anthem.

Next up, we welcome upcoming UK producer and Middleton’s own tipped talent, Geode, with his garage infused club roller, awash with wavering synths and quirky percussive licks.

Anjunadeep legend Vincenzo returns the favour following Tom’s much-loved 2012 remix of ’Sometimes Saturday', offering up a signature melodic rework, complimenting the spacey atmospherics of the original with a hallmark deep rolling bassline. Debuted by James Grant during his live set at Anjunadeep Miami, Vincenzo's deep house cut has already begun the rounds, a peak summer gem.

tracks.tag_list: journeyman get closer sideways
tracks.title: Journeyman - Sideways
tracks.description:
Journeyman are a new production duo from London. Formed at the end of 2012 they moved straight into the spotlight with their killer remix of Drum & Bass anthem Carry Me On by Brookes Brothers feat. Chrom3, earning them specialist support from the likes of B.Traits and Andy Durrant.

Journeyman are now set to make their full artist debut on NewState Music, with the release of double a-side single: Get Closer / Sideways.

Kicking off proceedings is ‘Get Closer’, an immersive slice of future house music, featuring the sultry vocals of Claudia Georgette. This classy track fuses some of their influences, which range from soul and jazz to classical, resulting in this top-notch production.

Sideways is a weightier house workout that heads straight to the club. This banger features further trademark bleeps, cut up chanting vocals, and one of the best basslines you’ll hear this year!

Both tracks come with radio, club, and instrumental mixes.

Formed by a combination of an old friendship and a passion for music, the duo took their production name from the old boxing term ‘Journeyman’.

Under various guises, Journeyman have already achieved success in other electronic genres, racking up playlist support on Radio 1 & 1Xtra and playing to masses of fans at festivals, and clubs all over the globe.

This level of musical experience and maturity is highlighted and reflected in the Journeyman sound: it has warmth, depth, and does damage on the dancefloor.

This debut release is set to be a future classic, with the enigmatic Journeyman poised to become one of the most exciting new forces in the house music scene.

tracks.tag_list: "Pete Oak" Tranquila Steyoyoke "Steyoyoke Black" SYYKBLK002 Dahu Remix
tracks.title: Pete Oak - Tranquila (Dahu Remix)
tracks.description:
iTUNES: http://smarturl.it/syykblk002_itunes
STEYOYOKE SHOP: http://smarturl.it/syykblk002_shop
BEATPORT: http://smarturl.it/syykblk002_beatport
VIDOE TEASER: http://smarturl.it/syykblk002_teaser
DJ FEEDBACKS: http://smarturl.it/syykblk002_feedbacks

Artist: Pete Oak
Title: Tranquila
Label: Steyoyoke Black
Format: Digital
Digital Release Date: Oct 6th, 2014
Cat No: SYYKBLK002

Steyoyoke Black continues to make its presence known and with the wind of success in their sails they charge full steam ahead with their second release, which has already featured in Finnbassen's latest BBC Radio 1 podcast for Pete Tong. The 'Tranquila' EP by Pete Oak features one original and one remix, with Dahu stepping forth for remix duties. 'Tranquila' is an EP that brings together not one, but two princes of darkness who perfectly reflect the sinister sounds now bound to Steyoyoke Black.

'Tranquilla' is an ode to Pete Oak's production skills and is indeed something to be admired. The rhythm is sharp, intense and demanding, with a heavy dose of percussion to help accentuate a strong sense of mystique and power. The bassline rolls and lolls, sucking into a hole of techno driven darkness. 

Dahu's remix can best be described as liquid gold to the ears. He chooses to expose 'Tranquila's underlying attitude and majestic beauty, which makes you want to close your eyes at times to fully absorb its melodic groove. Strings, high hats and layered synths overlap a cascade of chord progressions, that gradually push you to a point of no return.

TRACKLIST
01. Pete Oak - Tranquila (Original Mix)
02. Pete Oak - Tranquila (Dahu Remix)

tracks.tag_list: Electronic
tracks.title: Lane 8 - Ghost ft. Patrick Baker (Lane 8 Rework)
tracks.description:
Beatport: po.st/GhostRemixes
Release Date: 18th May 2015

Rising Anjunadeep star Lane 8 announced the release of his debut album in style recently, with the brilliant new single ‘Ghost feat. Patrick Baker’. On remix duties are a diverse trio of talented producers; techno innovator Audion, Aus Music prodigy Bwana and blogger's favourite Luvian.

After collaborating with Lane 8 on a track on the upcoming album, Matthew Dear took to his notorious Audion guise to remix ‘Ghost’, following remixes for legendary acts like Leftfield, Four Tet, Dubfire and Seth Troxler. Completely twisting the mood of the original, cutting the vocal over a frenetic groove he delivers a gnarly late-night techno cut.

Bwana has marked himself out as one to watch with his excellent EPs on Will Saul’s Aus Music, and his epic take on ‘Ghost’ is another winner, playing off the subtle melodies of the original with a huge bass hook, and Patrick Baker’s evocative lyrics.

UK based Luvian has been bubbling away for a while, with his early tracks picking up millions of plays on YouTube and Soundcloud. He takes his remix away from the club, instead opting for a gorgeous poolside version, stripping back almost entirely to sparse percussion, sensual melodic textures and warped vocals.

tracks.title: Yotto - Azzurro [BBC Radio 1 Premiere]
tracks.description:
Pre-order Anjunadeep 07: http://po.st/Anjunadeep07
Release Date: 25 May
Beatport: http://po.st/MementoAzzurro

Talented Helsinki producer Yotto aka Otto Yliperttula is the latest signing to the Anjunadeep roster, debuting with a heavy-hitting two tracker “Memento / Azzurro”. 

First heard in James Grant’s Anjunadeep Edition 50 mix “Memento” is a huge dancefloor weapon, echoing the bass-driven sounds of Jonas Rathsman and Dusky. Rolling low-end stabs surge through murky, atmospheric melodies leading to an epic breakdown.

“Azzurro” is another bass heavy roller, built around a growling groove that gives way to a nostalgic piano line and soaring pads, rising to a dramatic crescendo before dropping back into darkness.

tracks.tag_list: House Edm cassie Remix WHTKD
tracks.title: Cassie - Me & U (WHTKD Remix)
Greg Downey & Bo Bruce - These Hands I Hold (Paul Oakenfold Future House Mix)
tracks.description:
Having come second in a recent series of the BBC hit talent series “The Voice” as well as then going on to collaborate on numerous hits with the likes of Gareth Emery, Kryder, Chicane and Simon Patterson, Bo Bruce is a name that is already widely known in the music industry today. 

Here she makes her Perfecto debut teaming up with Trance veteran Greg Downey to produce “These Hands I Hold” - a sublime remake of an uber hot track taken from her first artist album  “Before I Sleep” on Mercury Records. 

This is a melodic monster with blissfully spine tingling vocals layered on beautifully energetic beats.  

Already snapped up for use as an exclusive on Simon Patterson’s recent Ministry of Sound – Trance Nation 2015 compilation, the original is now joined by a delicious collection of remixes from some of the hottest names on the label. 

First up, Paul Oakenfold’s Future House remix follows on in the style of his recent hit with Angela McCluskey that saw four consecutive weekly plays on Pete Tong’s BBCR1 Essential Selection. This is a radio and club friendly interpretation for fans of quality house music. 

Trance heavyweight Sean Tyas makes his debut on Perfecto with a stunning peak time high energy makeover while Johnny Yono returns with an epic trademark melodic feast in the flavour of his recent successful “Poison Whispers EP”. 

Roddy Reynaert does what he does best delivering a high quality progressive chugger that will surely reach far and wide this summer. 

A huge release in time for the festival season  - enjoy!

Having launched its record label arm back in 2014 and counting releases from the likes of Just Kiddin, Ten Ven and Tommy Vercetti, Eton Messy are to round off 2015 by welcoming Kayper back to their influential imprint for her latest offering, ’What You Say’. 
 
A follow-up to the June release of ’Terminal’ - which received wide support from Monki, Pete Tong and Annie Nightingale - ’What You Say’ builds on the fledgling producer’s taste for nostalgic, feel-good house music,  accompanied by the smooth vocals of previous collaborator Jonny Winston. With Kayper also scheduled to appear at a range of dates across the upcoming Eton Messy Winter Tour in London, Manchester and Bristol, her second release on Eton Messy Records looks set to be equally as promising as the first.

tracks.tag_list: Mickey "You Know The Beat" Exploited Deep House Berlin
tracks.title: Mickey - You Know The Beat
tracks.description:
Beatport - www.beatport.com/release/you-know-the-beat/1441785

iTunes - Pre Order - bit.ly/YouKnowTheBeat

'Belgian producer Mickey makes music that's just like his country's chocolate: sweet, smooth and oh-so-enticing. Last year's Exploited releases 'LA Anyway' and 'Holding Hands', especially the latter, are exactly that, not forgetting the stunning 'Sweet Baby' and remixes of Sébastien Tellier and Claptone.
Another Exploited release, 'You Know The Beat', is coming this month and it's a lively, juicy fruit slab of bumpin' house. This guy's roll ain't ending any time soon by the sound of things.' (Mixmag)

'This irresistable piece of funked up house music comes from one of our favourite artists, Mickey. Always delivering freshness, Exploited team up with him again for another unbeatable release. We love this track and will be playing it all year, ideal for brightening up a dreary winter’s day!' WORD UP.' (Deephouse London)

'The general trend in house music as of late has been a bit on the dark side but it doesn’t mean that the best music has been in that territory. Top pick of the week is by the Belgian producer simply known as Mickey who is back on Exploited with this disco-funk jam called “You Know The Beat”.' (Magnetic Magazine)

Featured on upcoming DJMag Selection 01 Compilation + early support by BBC Radio1/Danny Howard, dOP, Erol Alkan, Totally Enormous Extinct Dinosaurs, Martin Landsky, Laurent Garnier, Tensnake, Riva Starr, ZDS, Arthur Baker, Miguel Campbell, DJ T, Sasha, Bag Raiders, Wildkats, Kasper Bjoerke, Waifs & Strays, Noir, Mia Dora, Laidback Luke, Sonny Fodera, James Curd, Moodymanc, Pezzner, Kyodai, Nils Nuernberg, Crackazat, Brett Johnson, Compuphonic, James Curd, PJU, Jamie Anderson, Sinden, Phonique, Khan, Smash TV.

Mickey starts the New Year with another great anthem. 'You Know The Beat' is a mixup of 90ies French House, combined with a classic old school American House Vibe and Groove. Think Cassius meets Todd Terry.

We saw Mickey, as a newcomer, growing on the label Exploited. His releases 'Sweet Baby', 'Holding Hands' and 'Walk Away' are topping our label's bestsellers of the year 2014. His track 'Sweet Baby' was among the Top 10 best selling tracks at Beatport in the genre Deephouse. Next to his Belgian residency at the infamous 'Libertine Supersport' nights, he travels all over the world to rock the crowd with his energetic DJ sets.

He just finished a remix for Australian 'Modular Label‘ stars 'Bag Raiders' and is currently in London working on his next single.

Design by Neven Cvijanovic / Floor 5. Illustration by Laura Junger.

tracks.title: Siege - Yeah (Original Mix)
tracks.description:
Siege - Yeah (Original Mix)

Out Now: https://fanlink.to/BB024 

Belgian DJ/Producer Siege joins the Brobot Records family with the release of his latest single “Yeah,” out now.

Fresh off its 2-year anniversary, Brobot Records, the label headed by Junior Sanchez, will be celebrating another exceptional year in 2016. The imprint has hosted some of the biggest names in house music including Harry Romero, Felix Da Housecat, Alexander Technique and Blaqwell.

Having already seen major support on BBC Radio 1 from the likes of Pete Tong, Annie Mac and Danny Howard, Siege’s “Yeah” single consists of two tracks – the title track is marked by a swinging bassline and a chopped up soul sample that gives it a warm, infectious feeling. The Junior Sanchez remix of the original is full of classic tracky US house vibes that is sure to get dance floors from New York to LA and everywhere else in between moving.

Brobot Records has also proved time and time again their pristine knack for spotting new talent early on, adding Siege to their roster. Born and bred in Belgium, it was from a very early age that Siege’s eyes opened to the world of Dance. As every young Dance music fan does he gathered his life savings and invested in a set of turntables. Since then Siege has remixed the likes of Rudimental, Charlie XCX and Kaz James. His last release ‘Crunk’ chalked up a Beatport top 10, spending 5 weeks in the House Chart top 10.

For more information on Siege, please visit:

tracks.title: Camelphat - The Quad (Original Mix)
tracks.description:
The Camelphat guys are absolutely killing it right now. "It Is What It Is" is a brilliantly uncomplicated club track. Like "French Kiss" or SIL's "Windows" from the 90s or Gorge's "Tayo" or "Rollox" by Adriatique from now, this is a gold-plated DJ weapon. For those looking for something a bit sassier, "No One Hears You" delivers a half-time-Superbowl of a track with loopy keys and bouncing bass. Lastly "The Quad" is the kind of simple-but-beautiful piano anthem that's perfect if you're in a simple-but-off-your-face kind of mood. 

Support from: Groove Aramada, Claptone, Mark Knight, Hector Romero, Waifs & Strays, Mat.Joe, Paul Harris, TCTS, Junior Sanchez, PANDA, Illyus & Barrientos, Low Steppa, DJ T, Russ Chimes, Benoit Tsugi, Dale Middleton, Solaris Heights, Vanilla Ace, No Artificial Colours, Brett Gould, Factomania, Kal Jhugroo (Underground Audio), Timo Garcia, Taku Takahashi, George Wedd / Eton Messy, Steve Lawler, Eddie M...
